                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.11/3778.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Canada</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Vera Cruz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-24T14:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 24, 1914, 2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Now advised by Admiral Badger plan send war vessel to Frontera and other places
                    not feasible owing possible incitement Mexicans <pb facs="0791" n="675"
                        xml:id="pg_675"/> against Americans. The Admiral is prepared when authorized
                    and strongly recommends that such authorization be given to charter a steamer
                    here to be sent immediately for these refugees who will be taken care of here on
                    arrival. Please rush reply. Steamer can probably be secured for three to four
                    hundred dollars gold a day exclusive of provisions and coal.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Canada</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
